FREssay: My future self is someone who knows what they want out of life and is on the way to getting it. She is focused and determined. Feeling connected to this is good for me because it helps me achieve more things. If I act like my future self, I'll be able to become the future self I want to be. I will be able to do things without procrastination and stick with my plans.

FFEssay: She is diligent and pays attention to details.  She eats healthy food.  She exercises every day.  She goes to bed early and wakes up early.  She is financially responsible.  She cleans up after herself an her pets every night.  She makes time every day to learn new things.

PFPast: I believe that it is important to learn from past experiences.  My past self was more implusive, which I need to be more of sometimes.  However, my past self also made his share of mistakes.  Which is something I can remember and learn from.  It is good to remember past experiences to help you with new ones.

I recall being a procrastinator as my past self. I think the benefits to feeling connected to my past is knowing not to make the same mistakes. I know not to become a procrastinator again because it negatively affects your life. I think it might be good to act like your past self when you have your life set up to being able to afford to act like your past self. My past self is good at being able to remember things and having a good memory.

FFEssay: The benefits of feeling connected to my future self are being better able to visualize and stick to a path to becoming my future self. It would be good for me to act like my future self most of the time as my suture self is much more driven and successful than I currently am. Tasks that keeping my future self in mind as a role model are building things and improving my property, sticking to tasks at hand and working har, and planning out changes that I want to make soon. My future self is a much better handyman and farmer than I am now, who makes good money from a variety of sources and is very independent.

FREssay: The benefits to feeling connected to my future is that only I know what I want and who I want to be. Everyday is a good time as you progress to be the best version of yourself. I believe my future self would be good at understanding situations and putting things in perspective. My future self would be a very big motivation for me to better myself. I believe that's a great way to be happy.

PFPast: Benefits of connecting to my past include most importantly learning from my own mistakes. It might be good to "act like" my old self at times when I am repeating something that was successful in the past. Using my past self would be most motivating in that I would definitely be able to more easily recognize errors or actions by myself and others that I would not want to replicate. It could help in areas of education, work, and also in issues of family matters and friendships as well. My past self was good at being motivated in my educational and professional pursuits. I was also very good at compartmentalizing difficult situations and relationships, and I was able to be successful against some emotionally difficult odds.

PREssay: I used to make more time for myself. I have three children and since I started a family I have almost completely neglected my past interests in art and fulfilling my creative needs. I think it would be great for me to act like my old very creative self. I think the best thing to do that would help me be more like my past self would be to take an art class or finally learn a coding program. I should set time aside every day to be artistic in some way. I used to be very good at drawing, painting, pastels, chalk. It was very fun and rewarding and I really am missing that aspect of my life.
